1
00:00:01,520 --> 00:00:03,560
Why do I have to play
this stupid game with you?

2
00:00:03,640 --> 00:00:04,936
Because this'll be a long conversation,

3
00:00:04,960 --> 00:00:06,920
both about the song and Po.

4
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:08,280
Stop nitpicking me already.

5
00:00:08,360 --> 00:00:09,840
You don’t even have feelings for him.

6
00:00:12,720 --> 00:00:14,200
What if I do?

7
00:00:15,360 --> 00:00:17,816
I thought you were going to accuse me of
jumping to conclusions about Thame again.

8
00:00:17,840 --> 00:00:19,120
I won’t scold you anymore.

9
00:00:19,760 --> 00:00:20,840
Why?

10
00:00:20,920 --> 00:00:21,960
It’s because I’ve realized

11
00:00:22,440 --> 00:00:24,080
you’re not just imagining it on your own.

12
00:00:28,040 --> 00:00:30,760
I also remember our movie date promise.

13
00:00:30,840 --> 00:00:34,320
Can I watch this movie
in your room tonight?

14
00:00:38,160 --> 00:00:39,840
-Just one box, right? -Yes.

15
00:00:58,840 --> 00:01:00,120
My room is a mess.

16
00:01:00,720 --> 00:01:02,040
I didn’t expect anyone to come.

17
00:01:02,920 --> 00:01:04,176
Can you close your eyes for a second?

18
00:01:04,200 --> 00:01:05,319
Give me two minutes.

19
00:01:26,600 --> 00:01:27,760
It's not messy at all.

20
00:01:40,640 --> 00:01:43,920
If we're using this one, you
don’t need to tidy up the rest.

21
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:45,400
That way, we won’t finish too late.

22
00:01:47,800 --> 00:01:48,880
Well…

23
00:01:52,360 --> 00:01:53,360
Well,

24
00:01:54,680 --> 00:01:56,600
how about we eat something first?

25
00:01:56,680 --> 00:01:58,360
You haven’t eaten anything, right?

26
00:01:58,440 --> 00:01:59,880
You must be hungry.

27
00:01:59,960 --> 00:02:02,440
I’ll… find you something to eat.

28
00:02:32,720 --> 00:02:34,200
It’s nice.

29
00:02:34,280 --> 00:02:35,440
We can adjust the light, too.

30
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:40,560
How bright do you want it?

31
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:45,480
That’s up to you.

32
00:02:48,440 --> 00:02:51,080
If we make it completely dark,
I think the mood will be better.

33
00:02:53,720 --> 00:02:54,720
But…

34
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:57,080
since it’s our first time,

35
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:04,320
I’d rather see your face clearly.

36
00:03:06,480 --> 00:03:07,720
-Ouch! -Hey!

37
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:12,920
- Hey, relax. Hey.
- Take it off or your skin will swell.

38
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:14,000
Hey.

39
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:30,240
Huh? It doesn't feel hot?

40
00:03:31,480 --> 00:03:33,120
It doesn’t.

41
00:03:35,720 --> 00:03:37,440
Good thing I didn’t plug it in.

42
00:03:38,360 --> 00:03:39,640
I’ll make a new one for you.

43
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:41,440
You should clean up.

44
00:03:42,480 --> 00:03:43,520
The bathroom’s over there.

45
00:03:43,560 --> 00:03:45,240
I’ll find you some clothes to change into.

46
00:03:46,280 --> 00:03:47,280
Okay.

47
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:37,160
I made you a late-night meal. Enjoy.

48
00:04:38,280 --> 00:04:40,720
How about you take a shower while I eat?

49
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:42,280
It’ll help you feel more comfortable.

50
00:06:26,520 --> 00:06:29,200
Why do you have so many
pictures of yourself crying?

51
00:06:31,920 --> 00:06:34,520
My mom told me I was such
a crybaby when I was a kid.

52
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:36,520
I’d cry over small things.

53
00:06:39,760 --> 00:06:41,040
What about now?

54
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:42,760
Are you still a crybaby?

55
00:06:45,200 --> 00:06:46,360
I’m not anymore.

56
00:06:47,160 --> 00:06:48,280
That’s good.

57
00:06:55,240 --> 00:06:56,240
What’s this?

58
00:06:57,320 --> 00:06:58,840
It’s a fabric sample book.

59
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:02,440
Uncle Joei gave it to me when I
first started working at his suit shop.

60
00:07:18,800 --> 00:07:20,200
Why are you enjoying it this much?

61
00:07:21,480 --> 00:07:22,760
I’m just happy

62
00:07:23,720 --> 00:07:24,880
to learn what you like.

63
00:07:30,680 --> 00:07:34,760
You kept the giveaway
with my picture on it?

64
00:07:36,400 --> 00:07:38,680
Oh, hey. It’s not what you think.

65
00:07:38,760 --> 00:07:41,520
Baifern hired me to design it,

66
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:43,000
so I kept it as a memory.

67
00:07:44,120 --> 00:07:45,640
It’s work I like.

68
00:07:49,720 --> 00:07:50,880
I mean it.

69
00:07:52,280 --> 00:07:53,840
I even kept the file.

70
00:07:56,800 --> 00:07:57,840
I believe you, then.

71
00:07:58,520 --> 00:08:00,240
I didn’t just make yours.

72
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:03,160
I made Jun’s too.

73
00:08:03,960 --> 00:08:05,040
Here.

74
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:09,960
Why does Jun’s say "One and Only",

75
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:12,560
while mine just says "Happy Birthday"?

76
00:08:13,560 --> 00:08:14,560
Well,

77
00:08:15,120 --> 00:08:16,520
that’s what the client asked for.

78
00:08:17,440 --> 00:08:18,520
How much did they hire you?

79
00:08:20,040 --> 00:08:21,440
I want one like this too.

80
00:08:23,320 --> 00:08:24,840
Thame.

81
00:08:24,920 --> 00:08:26,000
I’m being serious here.

82
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:34,600
Won’t you check the other shelves?

83
00:08:35,720 --> 00:08:37,039
I won’t.

84
00:08:37,120 --> 00:08:38,400
I want to watch a movie now.

85
00:08:39,039 --> 00:08:40,919
I need to forget what
just burned into my mind.

86
00:08:42,039 --> 00:08:43,679
"One and only," whatever.

87
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:15,160
Did you go in there?

88
00:09:20,040 --> 00:09:21,040
I sure did.

89
00:09:23,800 --> 00:09:26,800
I went to get my money from the guard,
but I was kicked out not long after.

90
00:09:38,800 --> 00:09:39,800
I don't know.

91
00:09:40,600 --> 00:09:42,160
I guess it's just like any other hotel.

92
00:09:42,840 --> 00:09:44,000
Nothing special.

93
00:09:44,880 --> 00:09:46,320
How so?

94
00:09:48,320 --> 00:09:51,040
I don’t know if I’ll ever see the day that…

95
00:10:22,440 --> 00:10:23,560
You aren’t watching anymore?

96
00:10:29,080 --> 00:10:30,080
Well,

97
00:10:31,120 --> 00:10:33,520
I’m watching through the
reflection in your eyes.

98
00:11:07,080 --> 00:11:08,240
Let me…

99
00:11:31,880 --> 00:11:33,000
