00:21:39,040 --> 00:21:41,520
You're here to promote
your new single, right?

267
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:43,080
Please introduce your new single.

268
00:21:43,160 --> 00:21:44,416
TONIGHT, I’LL WATCH A MOVIE IN YOUR ROOM

269
00:21:44,440 --> 00:21:46,760
YEAH.

270
00:22:20,960 --> 00:22:22,240
Why are you laughing?

271
00:22:22,320 --> 00:22:23,320
I miss you.

272
00:22:24,440 --> 00:22:25,440
I miss you, too.

273
00:22:53,400 --> 00:22:54,240
Po!

274
00:22:54,320 --> 00:22:55,840
Open the door.

275
00:22:59,560 --> 00:23:00,880
Go hide.

276
00:23:04,080 --> 00:23:06,520
Po, what are you doing?

277
00:23:09,680 --> 00:23:10,840
Po!

278
00:23:11,520 --> 00:23:12,680
Po!

279
00:23:15,600 --> 00:23:16,440
Is something up?

280
00:23:16,520 --> 00:23:17,920
I’ve already figured out

281
00:23:18,000 --> 00:23:19,360
who Mr. A and Mr. B are.

282
00:23:32,360 --> 00:23:33,880
You’re Mr. A,

283
00:23:34,480 --> 00:23:39,640
and Mr. B is someone
connected to MARS, right?

284
00:23:40,680 --> 00:23:43,520
See? The first photo is from
around the group’s house.

285
00:23:43,600 --> 00:23:46,040
The second photo is from
your documentary filming job.

286
00:23:46,640 --> 00:23:48,680
The third photo has their items,

287
00:23:48,760 --> 00:23:50,960
shirt sleeves, and food.

288
00:23:51,040 --> 00:23:53,120
Do you think I won’t recognize them?

289
00:23:53,200 --> 00:23:55,240
I saw all those things
even before you knew them.

290
00:23:55,320 --> 00:23:56,496
This is pretty clear, don’t you think?

291
00:23:56,520 --> 00:23:58,720
Hold on, Fern. I can explain this.

292
00:23:58,800 --> 00:23:59,800
Stop.

293
00:23:59,880 --> 00:24:02,120
Then you suddenly got all into MARS.

294
00:24:02,720 --> 00:24:03,840
You voted, streamed,

295
00:24:03,920 --> 00:24:07,240
- and asked me to do it even before I did.
- Fern, listen up.

296
00:24:07,320 --> 00:24:08,320
Stop.

297
00:24:11,360 --> 00:24:13,000
You’re dating Mick, right?

298
00:24:13,080 --> 00:24:14,240
Huh?

299
00:24:15,760 --> 00:24:16,800
Am I right?

300
00:24:17,400 --> 00:24:18,456
I remember that shirt sleeve.

301
00:24:18,480 --> 00:24:20,720
He wore it when we met.

302
00:24:21,320 --> 00:24:24,200
Now, you’re helping Mick’s work, huh?

303
00:24:25,240 --> 00:24:28,040
-Well… -Well? Eh?

304
00:24:28,120 --> 00:24:29,640
Speechless?

305
00:24:29,720 --> 00:24:31,440
Come on, Po.

306
00:24:32,120 --> 00:24:33,200
Seriously?

307
00:24:33,280 --> 00:24:35,920
Mick is no different
from that jerk Earn at all.

308
00:24:36,000 --> 00:24:36,880
Please.

309
00:24:36,960 --> 00:24:38,696
If you’re going to be in a
relationship or date someone,

310
00:24:38,720 --> 00:24:40,600
find a better partner, okay?

311
00:24:40,680 --> 00:24:42,680
Gosh, my migraine is acting up.

312
00:24:42,760 --> 00:24:45,320
Hey. You’ve gone too far.

313
00:24:45,400 --> 00:24:47,720
Lately, more fans have been following me,

314
00:24:47,800 --> 00:24:50,040
so I preferred posting
on my close friend list.

315
00:24:50,560 --> 00:24:53,000
Some of those photos you
said have their arms and legs?

316
00:24:53,080 --> 00:24:54,280
Those are your photos.

317
00:24:54,880 --> 00:24:57,760
I can’t post them too obviously, or
else it’d be like dropping spoilers.

318
00:25:02,800 --> 00:25:03,960
Are you sure?

319
00:25:04,800 --> 00:25:06,040
Of course.

320
00:25:06,120 --> 00:25:07,120
Go back already.

321
00:25:07,160 --> 00:25:09,040
I’m busy. I’m about to go to bed.

322
00:25:09,120 --> 00:25:10,240
Let go!
I can walk by myself.

323
00:25:10,960 --> 00:25:12,280
Be careful of my face, okay?

324
00:25:14,480 --> 00:25:15,480
Hey!

325
00:25:16,080 --> 00:25:17,440
Shoot…

326
00:25:32,760 --> 00:25:36,000
I’m no longer a kid who will
just hide someone in my room.

327
00:25:39,400 --> 00:25:41,680
I didn’t think that

328
00:25:42,280 --> 00:25:43,720
you’re hiding him in your room.

329
00:25:49,400 --> 00:25:51,600
I’m just trying to look for some evidence,

330
00:25:51,680 --> 00:25:53,680
to see if I can find…

331
00:25:56,680 --> 00:25:58,520
something to pin on you.

332
00:26:00,320 --> 00:26:01,400
Let’s do this.

333
00:26:01,480 --> 00:26:04,600
If you want me to quickly
head back, admit it.

334
00:26:05,680 --> 00:26:07,320
I’m not in the talking stage with anyone.

335
00:26:16,920 --> 00:26:19,120
Then, why do you have two pillows?

336
00:26:20,640 --> 00:26:22,760
You usually keep that in your closet

337
00:26:23,360 --> 00:26:25,200
if nobody is sleeping over.

338
00:26:32,920 --> 00:26:33,920
Fern!

339
00:26:39,560 --> 00:26:40,800
Po, you…

340
00:26:40,880 --> 00:26:42,200
Hey, I can explain this.

341
00:26:42,280 --> 00:26:44,240
You’re getting back
together with that jerk Earn?

342
00:26:45,040 --> 00:26:48,520
This is his, and this one is also his.

343
00:26:50,160 --> 00:26:51,880
His pillow and these clothes,

344
00:26:54,720 --> 00:26:56,760
not to mention the sandwich
you once ate every day.

345
00:26:58,560 --> 00:26:59,480
Po!

346
00:26:59,560 --> 00:27:00,760
Ouch!

347
00:27:01,360 --> 00:27:02,760
Mick is even a better option.

348
00:27:02,840 --> 00:27:04,640
Why are you so worried
about that jerk, huh?

349
00:27:04,720 --> 00:27:06,320
No!

350
00:27:06,400 --> 00:27:07,816
We’re not getting back together, seriously.

351
00:27:07,840 --> 00:27:10,560
If you didn’t get back together
with him, did you do something else?

352
00:27:13,000 --> 00:27:13,840
No!

353
00:27:13,920 --> 00:27:15,920
Just leave, okay? You’re
suspecting nonsense.

354
00:27:16,000 --> 00:27:17,576
If you’re here just for
this, then just leave already.

355
00:27:17,600 --> 00:27:19,600
I have a meeting in ten minutes. Leave!

356
00:27:19,680 --> 00:27:20,720
Po!

357
00:27:33,840 --> 00:27:34,840
Thame.

358
00:27:35,400 --> 00:27:36,760
You can come out now.

359
00:27:36,840 --> 00:27:37,920
My friend left.

360
00:27:39,720 --> 00:27:40,720
No.

361
00:27:43,920 --> 00:27:44,920
Are you okay?

362
00:27:48,080 --> 00:27:49,640
The sandwich you bought for me

363
00:27:52,200 --> 00:27:53,920
is your ex’s favorite?

364
00:27:54,000 --> 00:27:55,120
Well,

365
00:27:56,080 --> 00:27:57,720
in the past, it was our favorite shop.

366
00:27:57,800 --> 00:27:58,800
Our?

367
00:28:03,720 --> 00:28:05,400
And why are you still keeping his clothes?

368
00:28:05,880 --> 00:28:07,560
It’s just clothes, Thame.

369
00:28:07,640 --> 00:28:09,080
And why are you still keeping them?

370
00:28:11,200 --> 00:28:12,320
Well…

371
00:28:14,760 --> 00:28:15,880
Which ones are his?

372
00:28:17,520 --> 00:28:18,520
This one is also his.

373
00:28:20,400 --> 00:28:21,400
Huh?

374
00:28:26,800 --> 00:28:27,840
Thame,

375
00:28:28,600 --> 00:28:32,480
it’s just comfy to wear,
so I didn’t throw it away.

376
00:28:33,120 --> 00:28:34,480
You’re still wearing his clothes?!

377
00:28:35,200 --> 00:28:36,520
Well, yes.

378
00:28:37,920 --> 00:28:40,120
I mean, I don’t wear them anymore.

379
00:28:40,640 --> 00:28:41,640
I don’t even use any.

380
00:28:42,960 --> 00:28:44,360
Keeping them takes up space, right?

381
00:28:45,840 --> 00:28:47,560
I’ll pack them tonight to donate.

382
00:29:00,000 --> 00:29:03,800
FOR DONATION

383
00:29:25,920 --> 00:29:26,920
I’ll be right back.

384
00:29:49,920 --> 00:29:51,120
You’ve got a new one now.

385
00:29:52,240 --> 00:29:53,280
Throw this one away.

386
00:29:54,520 --> 00:29:55,520
Okay.

387
00:29:56,080 --> 00:29:57,320
Come with me now.

388
00:29:57,840 --> 00:29:58,840
Where are we going?

389
00:30:00,120 --> 00:30:01,240
The sandwich shop.

390
00:30:08,280 --> 00:30:10,280
Bro, if this guy comes
to buy your sandwich again,

391
00:30:10,800 --> 00:30:12,280
don’t sell him tuna.

392
00:30:12,360 --> 00:30:13,680
He can’t eat tuna anymore.

393
00:30:14,560 --> 00:30:16,320
-He’s allergic to it. -Eh?

394
00:30:16,400 --> 00:30:17,800
You suddenly became allergic to it?

395
00:30:18,320 --> 00:30:19,320
Well…

396
00:30:19,360 --> 00:30:20,360
Yeah.

397
00:30:21,000 --> 00:30:22,000
He broke out in a rash.

398
00:30:23,560 --> 00:30:27,280
From now on, just sell
him his regular order, BLT.

399
00:30:27,360 --> 00:30:28,600
As for the other…

400
00:30:32,200 --> 00:30:33,360
What does he not like to eat?

401
00:30:33,440 --> 00:30:34,440
Well,

402
00:30:35,600 --> 00:30:36,720
he doesn’t eat beef.

403
00:30:37,320 --> 00:30:39,320
Yeah. The other one
must be steak and cheese,

404
00:30:39,400 --> 00:30:40,680
the one and only, forever.

405
00:30:40,760 --> 00:30:41,776
This exact order only, okay?

406
00:30:41,800 --> 00:30:44,800
He won’t buy anything else because
he’s allergic to all the rest.

407
00:30:44,880 --> 00:30:45,920
Sure.

408
00:30:46,000 --> 00:30:47,200
Take two, then.

409
00:30:47,280 --> 00:30:48,896
I’ll give you extra since
the shop is closing soon.

410
00:30:48,920 --> 00:30:50,680
Please give me extra veggies.

411
00:30:50,760 --> 00:30:52,080
Sure.

412
00:31:03,920 --> 00:31:05,040
I’m sorry.

413
00:31:07,920 --> 00:31:09,320
You’re really angry, right?

414
00:31:12,720 --> 00:31:13,760
No.

415
00:31:15,400 --> 00:31:16,520
I’m mad because I’m jealous.

416
00:31:22,880 --> 00:31:23,880
Got it.

417
00:31:24,960 --> 00:31:26,280
Are you still smiling?

418
00:31:32,440 --> 00:31:34,160
Is there anything else we need to clear up?

419
00:31:35,080 --> 00:31:36,360
No more.

420
00:31:36,920 --> 00:31:38,280
My room is empty now.

421
00:31:44,840 --> 00:31:45,840
Let’s go then.

422
00:31:46,760 --> 00:31:47,760
Where again?

423
00:31:48,160 --> 00:31:50,000
Add my stuff to your room.

424
00:32:32,760 --> 00:32:34,480
"The sound of footsteps followed.

425
00:32:35,720 --> 00:32:37,640
He could no longer run forward.

426
00:32:38,720 --> 00:32:40,280
If he continued to run,

427
00:32:41,200 --> 00:32:43,040
it wouldn’t be long before they caught up."

428
00:32:45,120 --> 00:32:46,600
"The towering young man

429
00:32:47,400 --> 00:32:48,720
made his way into a house.

430
00:32:49,760 --> 00:32:51,240
When he stopped running,

431
00:32:52,320 --> 00:32:54,160
the chill crept in.

432
00:32:55,880 --> 00:32:58,160
The man walked over to the radiator…"

433
00:34:09,600 --> 00:34:12,120
Thanks for giving me the keycard.

434
00:34:19,199 --> 00:34:21,120
Now, it’ll be convenient
for you to come and go.

435
00:34:23,480 --> 00:34:26,440
Can we say I’m your boyfriend now?

436
00:34:33,600 --> 00:34:35,040
That’s up to you.

437
00:34:35,719 --> 00:34:38,000
I don’t know if you’re going
to call me that, but I will.

438
00:34:38,679 --> 00:34:39,719
My boyfriend.

439
00:34:44,239 --> 00:34:45,559
Go to Oner Entertainment, please.

440
00:34:55,600 --> 00:34:57,080
I’ll come to see you again tonight.

441
00:35:04,880 --> 00:35:06,176
The sequence is as we talked about.

442
00:35:06,200 --> 00:35:07,200
Got it.

443
00:35:13,080 --> 00:35:14,080
Hey,

444
00:35:14,960 --> 00:35:16,360
let’s do our best.

445
00:35:16,440 --> 00:35:17,440
If we win this chart,

446
00:35:18,000 --> 00:35:20,080
we stand a high chance to all-kill.

447
00:35:21,880 --> 00:35:23,240
I’m sure we can do it.

448
00:35:24,160 --> 00:35:25,160
Bros.

449
00:35:26,320 --> 00:35:27,376
Why are you looking so serious?

450
00:35:27,400 --> 00:35:30,040
Hey, I’m bringing you some drinks.

451
00:35:30,120 --> 00:35:32,400
Drink it before we perform,
so you’ll feel refreshed.

452
00:35:48,240 --> 00:35:49,560
Let’s get it!

453
00:35:51,560 --> 00:35:53,760
-One, two, three. -Yay!

