POP WEEKLY CHART | MUSIC OF THE
WEEK SONG: WHO SAYS - ARTIST: MARS

478
00:38:35,480 --> 00:38:36,480
Po!

479
00:39:15,040 --> 00:39:17,280
You finally won a music show.

480
00:39:17,360 --> 00:39:19,760
You should’ve gone out to
eat with your members instead.

481
00:39:20,920 --> 00:39:25,440
They said if we get an all-kill,
we’ll celebrate all at once later,

482
00:39:26,080 --> 00:39:27,880
so I told them I’d go to see you first.

483
00:39:27,960 --> 00:39:29,680
Per also wants to spend time with Gam.

484
00:39:31,520 --> 00:39:32,520
I see.

485
00:39:33,600 --> 00:39:34,960
I thought

486
00:39:35,560 --> 00:39:37,640
you’re taking me to eat at a secret place.

487
00:39:39,360 --> 00:39:40,880
I don’t do what Jun does.

488
00:39:41,400 --> 00:39:42,840
I have my own style.

489
00:40:00,640 --> 00:40:01,640
It’s delicious.

490
00:40:02,880 --> 00:40:04,600
I didn’t expect that you can cook.

491
00:40:06,200 --> 00:40:07,360
If you like it,

492
00:40:08,240 --> 00:40:10,200
I’ll practice and cook more dishes for you.

493
00:40:11,560 --> 00:40:13,360
Make time for some rest, okay?

494
00:40:14,560 --> 00:40:17,520
Just staying with you
and doing something for you

495
00:40:18,280 --> 00:40:20,240
makes me feel like I’m already resting.

496
00:40:21,800 --> 00:40:23,600
Are you exaggerating?

497
00:40:23,680 --> 00:40:24,840
I mean it.

498
00:40:26,440 --> 00:40:27,440
But…

499
00:40:27,960 --> 00:40:29,760
I want you to do
something for yourself, too.

500
00:40:30,600 --> 00:40:34,280
Being with you is what I do for myself.

501
00:41:09,240 --> 00:41:10,600
Did you go in there?

502
00:41:15,600 --> 00:41:16,600
I sure did.

503
00:41:19,440 --> 00:41:22,440
I went to get my money from the guard,
but I was kicked out not long after.

504
00:41:26,280 --> 00:41:27,280
Is it pretty inside?

505
00:41:34,400 --> 00:41:35,400
I don't know.

506
00:41:36,200 --> 00:41:39,080
I guess it's just like any
other hotel. Nothing special.

507
00:44:41,600 --> 00:44:43,080
Are you staying here for good?

508
00:44:43,160 --> 00:44:44,440
I want to, honestly.

509
00:44:48,520 --> 00:44:53,000
So, the traitor I’ve been searching
for isn’t Jun, but Po, right?

510
00:44:53,920 --> 00:44:54,920
What did you do to him?

511
00:44:55,440 --> 00:44:57,120
Leave all of MARS’ footage with Tae.

512
00:44:58,160 --> 00:44:59,600
You have no right to take any of it.

513
00:45:03,080 --> 00:45:05,000
We have to protect both
our dreams and our love.

514
00:45:05,560 --> 00:45:07,440
No matter what, we have
to make it work, right?
